    I'm saying,
    "You're welcome."

10:19.219 --> 10:20.652
     Hey, Barry,
     are you sure

10:20.654 --> 10:22.253
 this is how you want to
 spend your Saturday?

10:22.255 --> 10:24.923
   Dude. This movie
   is gonna be my calling card,

10:24.925 --> 10:27.025
    and it'll make
    Jamie Lee Curtis notice me.

10:27.027 --> 10:29.794
             Don't tell Lainey!
             No wait, tell her.
             She needs to know.

10:29.796 --> 10:32.998
 All right, first off,
 I wouldn't rock the boat
 of that relationship.

10:33.000 --> 10:36.968
 And secondly, I think I saw
 your Jenkintown Boys Club

10:36.970 --> 10:38.370
  down at the Wawa
  parking lot.

10:38.372 --> 10:40.472
          The JTP?
          Who was leading them?

10:40.474 --> 10:41.873
     I don't know.
     Some new guy.

10:41.875 --> 10:42.374
                    Was it Dan?
            Sure.

10:42.376 --> 10:45.777
         Stupid Dan!
         I will challenge him
         to a game of smashball

10:45.779 --> 10:47.345
     and reassert my dominance.

10:47.347 --> 10:47.779
         (TIRES SCREECH)

10:47.781 --> 10:50.048
     ADULT ADAM: <i> Turns out,</i>
    <i> when it came to being</i>
    <i> a producer,</i>

10:50.050 --> 10:52.417
    <i> my dad knew how to get</i>
    <i> exactly what he wanted.</i>

10:52.419 --> 10:55.420
 Why would he pass
 on the role of a lifetime?

10:55.422 --> 10:57.422
 Why?
 We're screwed blue!

10:57.424 --> 10:59.190
 We have no time to recast!

10:59.192 --> 11:00.158
          I'm way ahead of you.

11:00.160 --> 11:02.927
 Coach is here
 and ready for his closeup!

11:02.929 --> 11:04.796
 I am your clay.

11:04.798 --> 11:05.630
          Mold me.

11:05.632 --> 11:07.332
        Coach Mellor?
        He's our star?

11:07.334 --> 11:09.067
      Oh, yeah.
      I slipped him the script.

11:09.069 --> 11:09.968
          He responded
          to the material.

11:09.970 --> 11:15.040
 Well, I guess
 you're my only option,
 so...you got the part.

11:15.475 --> 11:17.409
                  You honor me.
 Do you know your lines?

11:17.411 --> 11:19.978
  I memorized the whole script.
  I love the zingers.

11:19.980 --> 11:22.947
             My favorite one...
             "See you ladle."

11:22.949 --> 11:26.851
   I like how you wrote "ladle"
   instead of "later."
   'Cause I'm a cook.

11:26.853 --> 11:28.953
 "See you ladle"?
 I didn't write that.

11:28.955 --> 11:32.023
      That'd be me.
      I did some noodling
      with the script, partner.

11:32.025 --> 11:33.458
  Dad! You can't
  rewrite my script!

11:33.460 --> 11:37.062
          But you didn't have
          any snappy one-liners
          like Arnold says.

11:37.064 --> 11:38.930
           That's the best part
           of an action movie.

11:38.932 --> 11:41.132
              Now you got
              a bunch of 'em.

11:41.501 --> 11:43.368
                Sear you later.

11:43.370 --> 11:45.170
                Spat-u-later.

11:46.006 --> 11:47.772
              Cheese ya grater.

11:47.774 --> 11:49.207
 They are all the same!

11:49.209 --> 11:53.078
 Dad, I appreciate the support,
 but this is still my movie.

11:53.080 --> 11:56.748
            Hey. Everyone knows
            that you're the
            creative vision

11:56.750 --> 11:58.349
          behind
         <i> "Recipe for Death 2."</i>

11:58.351 --> 12:00.418
 Two? We haven't even filmed
 part one.

12:00.420 --> 12:02.487
         The best action movies
         are always the sequel,

12:02.489 --> 12:04.656
 so we're just skipping ahead
 to the good stuff.

12:04.658 --> 12:06.458
     Know what?
     We're a team.

12:06.460 --> 12:10.095
 The important thing
 here is we're working on
 this together.

12:10.097 --> 12:11.996
 Pops, I need
 a new producer!

12:11.998 --> 12:13.732
           Huh?
           What am I producing?

12:13.734 --> 12:15.967
 80 bucks and no back talk.
                 I'm in.

12:15.969 --> 12:19.637
  ADULT ADAM: <i> While I had found</i>
<i> a way to push my dad</i>
<i> out of the picture,</i>

12:19.639 --> 12:22.607
   <i> Erica had finally found</i>
   <i> her new look.</i>

12:22.609 --> 12:23.908
      Find everything you need?

12:23.910 --> 12:25.777
 (GRUMBLING) Mmm-mmm.

12:25.779 --> 12:27.579
             We did. Thank you.

12:27.581 --> 12:28.646
       Whatever.

12:28.648 --> 12:29.247
 I have a coupon.

12:29.249 --> 12:31.750
     Oh. I'm sorry, this coupon
     is for Gimbels.

12:31.752 --> 12:35.053
 Correct.
 It's a competitor's coupon,
 so you match the price.

12:35.055 --> 12:37.322
 And when we're done here,
 I'm gonna need this back

12:37.324 --> 12:38.356
  so I can use it
  at other stores.

12:38.358 --> 12:40.892
        Yeah, we don't
        really consider Gimbels
        a competitor

12:40.894 --> 12:45.697
      because we're fresh
      and cool and hip and fun,
      and they're...closing.

12:45.699 --> 12:48.867
 Oh, God. Um. Just run
 the credit-card machine thing.

12:48.869 --> 12:50.101
 Let me get this straight.

12:50.103 --> 12:52.203
 Benetton thinks it's better
 than Gimbels

12:52.205 --> 12:55.807
 because you have
 all these glossy posters
 hanging around?

12:55.809 --> 12:58.543
 These kids were
 clearly dressed
 against their will.

12:58.545 --> 12:59.911
        Come on,
        make the ch-chunk.

12:59.913 --> 13:00.912
  This is bull corn.

13:00.914 --> 13:02.580
             Okay. I'm going to
             have to ask you

13:02.582 --> 13:04.516
          to take your business
          elsewhere.

13:04.518 --> 13:05.483
        Ho-ho!

13:05.485 --> 13:08.119
   You're banning me
   from your store?

13:08.121 --> 13:09.320
    No-no, sister.

13:09.322 --> 13:10.288
   I'm banning you.

13:10.290 --> 13:12.490
              You can't ban me.
      Oh, I just did.

13:12.492 --> 13:14.125
 You are Ban-itonned!

13:14.127 --> 13:15.326
             That's not a word.

13:15.328 --> 13:17.262
    Oh, it is now.
    I Bani-ton you

13:17.264 --> 13:21.299
 from having the pleasure of us
 in your store, sucka!

13:21.301 --> 13:22.300
 Come on, Erica.

13:22.302 --> 13:24.369
 The cu...I'm...
 BEVERLY: No!

13:24.371 --> 13:26.171
    ADULT ADAM: <i> While my mom</i>
   <i> was making a scene,</i>

13:26.173 --> 13:29.541
   <i> I was directing a scene</i>
   <i> of my own.</i>

13:29.543 --> 13:31.009
          We meet again, Blade.

13:31.011 --> 13:32.377
 Well, well, John Cook.

