          I kept whispering,
          "Boom" so you'd raise
          it out of frame.

14:02.275 --> 14:04.075
         Oh! I thought you
         were going like,

14:04.077 --> 14:07.045
     "Boom! We just got another
     great cinematic moment."

14:07.047 --> 14:08.847
      Ah. What's all this?

14:08.849 --> 14:10.215
          Oh! Hey!
          I thought sending you

14:10.217 --> 14:13.818
   to get donuts at the airport
   would take much longer.

14:13.820 --> 14:16.187
    You're shooting movies
    without me?

14:16.189 --> 14:16.721
              Kinda.

14:16.723 --> 14:19.090
      I thought we were doing
      this whole deal together.

14:19.092 --> 14:22.493
 Uh. I decided to go
 with a different producer.

14:22.495 --> 14:24.162
              (MUMBLING)
              I have no notes.

14:24.164 --> 14:25.697
             I love everything
             the kid does.

14:25.699 --> 14:28.933
            I don't get it.
            You said you wanted
            my support.

14:28.935 --> 14:31.269
    I do! I...I did.
    I don't.

14:31.271 --> 14:32.904
            You can't give back
            support.

14:32.906 --> 14:34.205
          I just did.
                     No!

14:34.207 --> 14:35.406
          You keep the support!

14:35.408 --> 14:36.674
           And you're gonna get
           much more!

14:36.676 --> 14:38.710
          I'm gonna support you
          but good!

14:38.712 --> 14:39.611
 Don't you dare say that!

14:39.613 --> 14:43.181
              Oh, you heard me!
              I'm a big blanket
              of support!

14:43.183 --> 14:44.482
                A big blanket!

14:44.484 --> 14:45.550
     You monster.

14:45.552 --> 14:48.086
              Fine!
              Do what you want.

14:48.421 --> 14:52.824
        Also, you got some kind
        of bag so I can bring
        home this fruit?

14:52.826 --> 14:54.692
           You sure about this?
          Oh, I'm sure.

14:54.694 --> 14:56.895
 My mom gets me banned
 from Benetton?

14:56.897 --> 14:59.397
 Then I'll just bring
 Benetton to me.

14:59.399 --> 15:03.001
 Uh (SCOFFS)
 you can't just make
 a sweater dress.

15:03.003 --> 15:04.502
                   Can't I?

15:05.005 --> 15:05.570
     ADULT ADAM: <i> She could.</i>

15:05.572 --> 15:09.374
   <i> My sister had access</i>
   <i> to the biggest, loudest</i>
   <i> sweater collection</i>

15:09.376 --> 15:10.775
     <i> in the greater</i>
     <i> Philadelphia area.</i>

15:10.777 --> 15:14.445
   She has a sweater
   that celebrates the culture
   of sweaters?

15:14.447 --> 15:15.413
    My mind is melting!

15:15.415 --> 15:17.515
        Hey.
        This one shows promise.

15:17.517 --> 15:20.018
 Yeah, but those sleeves.
 Blech.

15:20.020 --> 15:21.419
        But...

15:21.421 --> 15:22.687
 if you took these sleeves

15:22.689 --> 15:24.555
 and the bottom half
 of this sparkly one,

15:24.557 --> 15:25.356
 that could totally
 be a dress!

15:25.358 --> 15:27.825
   And if you took the
   rhinestones from this one...

15:27.827 --> 15:30.795
 And used this fringe
 and these ruffles

15:30.797 --> 15:34.232
  and these weird tiny pockets,
  that would totally work!

15:34.234 --> 15:35.099
                   So cute!

15:35.101 --> 15:36.334
 ADULT ADAM: <i> And so they sewed.</i>

15:36.336 --> 15:38.102
  <i> They searched. They glued.</i>

15:38.104 --> 15:40.438
     <i> They ripped, snipped,</i>
     <i> and glittered.</i>

15:40.440 --> 15:41.706
 Okay. The big reveal.

15:41.708 --> 15:44.842
 Eat your heart out, Bene...
 Oh, my God!

15:45.211 --> 15:46.577
             This did not work!

15:46.579 --> 15:47.412
    No, it did not!

15:47.414 --> 15:49.013
             This does not look
             like Benetton!

15:49.015 --> 15:49.580
   No, it does not!

15:49.582 --> 15:51.215
      We need to cut up
      more sweaters and fix it!

15:51.217 --> 15:52.617
   ADULT ADAM:
  <i> And so they did it again.</i>

15:52.619 --> 15:55.520
   <i> They sewed,</i>
   <i> they cut, they tore.</i>

15:55.522 --> 15:57.055
 <i> They generally made a mess...</i>

15:57.057 --> 16:00.591
 <i> until they got it just right.</i>

16:00.694 --> 16:02.527
              (VOICE BREAKING)
              I made it worse.

16:02.529 --> 16:04.429
    You really did!

16:04.864 --> 16:06.297
               Why?

16:06.299 --> 16:07.198
              Why?

16:07.200 --> 16:08.733
           (GASPS)
           My sweaters!

16:08.735 --> 16:10.134
       My glorious sweaters!

16:10.136 --> 16:13.504
   I'm realizing now this whole
   thing got away from me.

16:13.506 --> 16:14.672
    Gimbels is out of business!

16:14.674 --> 16:17.809
 I can't replace them.
 They're all I had.

16:17.811 --> 16:19.677
             It's not my fault!

16:19.679 --> 16:20.478
             I mean, it is.

16:20.480 --> 16:23.247
   What I did sucks,
   but what you did sucks, too!

16:23.249 --> 16:24.716
        You got me Ban-itonned!

16:24.718 --> 16:25.516
  That is not a word.

16:25.518 --> 16:27.685
  And I thought that
  the most important thing

16:27.687 --> 16:29.020
    was us spending time
    together.

16:29.022 --> 16:31.956
   What mattered was the dress!
   Not you!

16:36.096 --> 16:37.428
             Fine.

16:38.098 --> 16:39.530
          (SMACKS LIPS)

16:39.532 --> 16:41.132
        Go buy it.

16:41.334 --> 16:44.702
   Hope you feel good knowing
   the real price you paid.

16:45.472 --> 16:46.804
 I think the price was her.

16:46.806 --> 16:48.873
      I know the price, Lainey!

16:50.343 --> 16:52.577
  ADULT ADAM: <i> It had been a day</i>
<i> since me and my sister</i>

16:52.579 --> 16:54.345
      <i> tricked our parents</i>
      <i> into supporting us.</i>

16:54.347 --> 16:57.482
   <i> And now my mom and dad were</i>
   <i> farther from us than ever.</i>

16:57.484 --> 17:00.451
    Look at her. She's not even
    Parming the shrimp.

17:00.453 --> 17:02.653
        Without her Parm,
        it's just plain shrimp.

17:02.655 --> 17:04.188
 Wow, you really
 messed her up.

17:04.190 --> 17:05.757
                Wow, you really
                messed him up.

17:05.759 --> 17:10.094
 He's wearing pants and not
 touching his rocky road?

17:10.096 --> 17:11.429
   This is bad.

17:11.431 --> 17:11.996
                This is awful.

17:11.998 --> 17:13.631
    All I wanted was for my mom
    to leave me alone.

17:13.633 --> 17:16.701
 All I wanted was
 for my dad to be
 a little more involved.

17:16.703 --> 17:18.236
 Now I've completely
 pushed him away.

17:18.238 --> 17:20.338
 I know this is the last thing
 you want to hear,

17:20.339 --> 17:22.940
 but you've gotta figure out
 a way to make her feel good.

17:22.942 --> 17:24.842
          Just figure out a way
          to get him back.

17:24.844 --> 17:26.644
           Damn it, why are you
           always right?

17:26.646 --> 17:27.878
 Damn it, you're right.

17:27.881 --> 17:28.946
       'Sup?
            What the...

17:28.948 --> 17:29.981
          Where'd you
          come from?

17:29.983 --> 17:31.883
  Dad said Dan
  took over the JTP,

17:31.885 --> 17:33.951
 and I had to stop him
 at all costs.

17:33.953 --> 17:34.819
                  Who's Dan?
     No idea.

17:34.821 --> 17:37.088
  So I gave everyone in school
  named Dan a wedgie.

17:37.090 --> 17:38.790
        Look.
        Movie's done, bro.

17:38.792 --> 17:39.557
  Damn you, Stallone!

17:39.559 --> 17:42.794
 I assume he took the part
 after I fell out!

17:44.364 --> 17:45.596
 Get your coat.
 We're going shopping.

17:45.598 --> 17:49.167
       Nice try. I'm done being
       used for my charge card.

17:49.169 --> 17:51.002
  Actually, this time
  it's my treat.

17:51.004 --> 17:54.539
 The Gimbels downtown
 store is having a
 going-out-of-business sale.

17:54.541 --> 17:57.341
 One day only.
 Everything 50% off.

17:57.343 --> 17:58.810
             Big whoop.
             Sales come and go.

17:58.812 --> 18:00.244
 I also believe you've
 been collecting

18:00.246 --> 18:02.980
 a lifetime of coupons,
 one of which is good

18:02.982 --> 18:05.883
 for 50% off
 your entire purchase.

18:05.885 --> 18:07.085
         Again, not interested.

18:07.087 --> 18:09.921
 You should also know
 that I called my old
 Gimbels manager

18:09.923 --> 18:13.224
 and he said he would honor
 my employee discount.

18:13.226 --> 18:15.560
  Another 50% off.

18:15.562 --> 18:17.829
         That's half of half of
         half off.

18:17.831 --> 18:18.963
         The shopping trifecta.

18:18.965 --> 18:21.866
       Only the luckiest yentas
       ever get to see it.

18:21.968 --> 18:23.601
 I know I messed up.

18:23.603 --> 18:27.205
 But what do you say
 we go do some damage?
 Together.

18:27.207 --> 18:29.273
                Let's go make
                some memories!

18:29.275 --> 18:31.309
    ADULT ADAM:
   <i> That day, my mom and sister</i>

18:31.311 --> 18:34.145
   <i> went on the shopping spree</i>
   <i> of a lifetime.</i>

18:34.147 --> 18:36.380
    <i> Racks were emptied,</i>
    <i> displays were toppled,</i>

18:36.382 --> 18:41.552
  <i> sweaters were replaced,</i>
  <i> and carts were overflowing.</i>

18:41.554 --> 18:42.353
                  Go, go, go!

18:42.355 --> 18:43.688
       Housewares up ahead!
       I'm on it!

18:43.690 --> 18:45.990
  <i> � All I need is a miracle �</i>

18:45.992 --> 18:48.025
         (MUSIC CUTS OUT)
 The reason
 he's cheating on you

18:48.027 --> 18:49.760
 is 'cause your house
 is so filthy.
                      Right?

18:49.762 --> 18:52.930
   This is my mom's!
   All of these are!

18:53.500 --> 18:54.532
    This is the proudest moment
    of my life.

18:54.534 --> 18:56.801
    ADULT ADAM: <i> And if Gimbels</i>
   <i> wasn't going out of</i>
   <i> business before,</i>

18:56.803 --> 19:02.340
   <i> they sure would have</i>
   <i> after my mom and sister</i>
   <i> were done there.</i>

19:02.742 --> 19:03.508
                     Yes!

19:03.510 --> 19:07.111
             (LAUGHING)
             We did it!
             We did it!

19:09.883 --> 19:11.249
              Hey, can we talk?

19:11.251 --> 19:12.984
     No talk.
     I'm fine.

19:12.986 --> 19:15.052
            Well, then just sit
            in your chair.

19:15.054 --> 19:16.787
 I've never said no to that.

19:16.789 --> 19:17.722
             I wanna show you
             something.

19:17.724 --> 19:21.425
   ADULT ADAM: <i> That something</i>
  <i> was my very first</i>
  <i> big-budget movie.</i>

19:21.427 --> 19:24.529
    <i> And I anxiously awaited</i>
    <i> the first review.</i>

19:24.797 --> 19:26.931
 <i> � All I need is a miracle</i>

19:26.933 --> 19:30.168
    <i> � All I need is you</i>

19:30.370 --> 19:32.937
 Wow. Your movie turned out
 really good.

19:32.939 --> 19:34.605
                  Our movie.

19:34.607 --> 19:36.240
    See you ladle.

19:36.242 --> 19:37.208
             (THUD)

19:37.210 --> 19:38.709
   Hey, you kept in
   my one-liners.

19:38.711 --> 19:41.746
     Yeah. You're a pretty good
     producer after all.

19:41.748 --> 19:43.848
      <i> � All I need is you</i>

19:43.850 --> 19:46.217
           Even though
           I kind of fired you,

19:46.219 --> 19:49.687
          it was really awesome
          having your support.

19:51.824 --> 19:52.757
       (SIGHS)

19:52.759 --> 19:54.492
 You know I'm not
 the kind of dad

19:54.494 --> 19:57.528
 who cheers and screams
 from the sidelines.

19:59.732 --> 20:03.634
 But it's really important
 for you to know

20:03.636 --> 20:06.837
 that I'll always be rooting
 for you.

20:07.574 --> 20:07.972
      Always.

20:07.974 --> 20:11.776
   <i> � I'm gonna love you</i>
   <i> for the rest of your life �</i>

20:15.148 --> 20:19.150
    ADULT ADAM: <i> That day,</i>
   <i> my mom got her</i>
   <i> picture-perfect ending.</i>

20:19.152 --> 20:21.686
     <i> Just not in the way</i>
     <i> she thought.</i>

20:22.355 --> 20:23.154
      <i> 'Cause in the end,</i>

20:23.156 --> 20:26.224
 <i> it's not about the costumes</i>
 <i> or the music,</i>

20:26.226 --> 20:28.426
    <i> or the explosions,</i>
    <i> for that matter.</i>

20:28.428 --> 20:30.294
     <i> It's the characters.</i>

20:30.296 --> 20:34.699
   <i> And in our house, you never</i>
   <i> had to look too far...</i>

20:34.701 --> 20:36.200
   I don't know
   how you did that.

20:36.202 --> 20:39.003
  <i> ...to find the perfect cast.</i>

